.TH "__devm_spi_alloc_controller" 9 "__devm_spi_alloc_controller" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
__devm_spi_alloc_controller \- resource-managed __spi_alloc_controller()
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct spi_controller *" __devm_spi_alloc_controller
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "unsigned int size "  ","
.BI "bool slave "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
physical device of SPI controller
.IP "size" 12
how much zeroed driver-private data to allocate
.IP "slave" 12
whether to allocate an SPI master (false) or SPI slave (true)
.SH "CONTEXT"
can sleep
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allocate an SPI controller and automatically release a reference on it
when \fIdev\fP is unbound from its driver.  Drivers are thus relieved from
having to call \fBspi_controller_put\fP.

The arguments to this function are identical to \fB__spi_alloc_controller\fP.
.SH "RETURN"
the SPI controller structure on success, else NULL.
